qas.question: When was the Canadian Joint Operations Command established?
What are the parts that merged into the Canadian Joint Operations Command?

answers.text: Canada Command, the Canadian Expeditionary Force Command and the Canadian Operational Support Command

qas.question: When was the non-Canadian Joint Operations Command established?

plausible_answers.text: Canada Command, the Canadian Expeditionary Force Command and the Canadian Operational Support Command

qas.question: What are the parts that merged into the non-Canadian Joint Operations Command?
What specifically didn't prompt this merger?

context: The Canadian Joint Operations Command is an operational element established in <a0_0><b3_0>October 2012<b3_0/><a0_0/> with the merger of <a1_0><b4_0>Canada Command, the Canadian Expeditionary Force Command and the Canadian Operational Support Command<b4_0/><a1_0/>. The new command, created as a response to the cost-cutting measures in <a2_0>the <b5_0>2012 federal budget<b5_0/><a2_0/>, combines the resources, roles and responsibilities of the three former commands under a single headquarters.
